This paper deals with joint source-channel coding for a multiple-access channel with correlated sources, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and communication theory (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the partitioning of messages into two classes, which is related to signal processing (cs.SI) and network information theory (cs.NI). Finally, the paper presents a system of equations to determine optimal thresholds, which is related to optimization (cs.CC).
